02:24.699 --> 02:26.867
So you found 11 feet so far?

02:26.934 --> 02:28.118
Yep.

02:28.203 --> 02:30.621
This whole yellow flag section
is our side.

02:30.705 --> 02:32.122
Rest of it's the Canadians.

02:32.207 --> 02:34.124
Well, unless it rained feet,

02:34.209 --> 02:36.210
these puppies definitely
washed ashore.

02:36.277 --> 02:38.996
Yeah, my trainee tripped over
one of them last night.

02:42.333 --> 02:43.917
I think I'll, uh,

02:43.968 --> 02:45.619
wait over there,
if that's okay with you.

02:45.670 --> 02:47.004
Yeah, right,
go grab yourself a donut.

02:47.088 --> 02:49.006
Based on the size,
this belonged to an adult male.

02:49.090 --> 02:50.007
Hmm.

02:50.091 --> 02:51.341
Given the range of motion

02:51.426 --> 02:53.460
of the metatarsophalangeal
joint, I'd say he was

02:53.511 --> 02:55.512
somewhere between 18 and 50.

02:55.580 --> 02:57.797
Great. That narrows it down
to about 50 million people.

02:59.517 --> 03:01.468
Yes, this appears to be a pair.

03:01.519 --> 03:02.519
Great, okay.

03:02.604 --> 03:04.238
Two down, 11 to go.

03:04.305 --> 03:05.522
Oh, nine to go.

03:05.607 --> 03:07.324
These boots are empty.
Hey, Bones,

03:07.408 --> 03:08.808
how much you want to bet
that those boots

03:08.860 --> 03:10.027
belong to Shoeless Joe
over there?

03:10.111 --> 03:12.696
Well, I'll see

03:12.780 --> 03:14.814
if the size of the boots

03:14.866 --> 03:16.033
conform to Joe.

03:16.117 --> 03:18.001
Okay?
Hey, B-Bones,

03:18.086 --> 03:20.087
you know, just, you know,
when you go over there,

03:20.154 --> 03:21.821
just be nice.
They're Canadians.

03:21.873 --> 03:23.624
You're referring to the
broad generalization

03:23.675 --> 03:25.325
that Canadians are polite?

03:25.376 --> 03:26.343
Yes, I am.

03:26.427 --> 03:27.461
Sorry, excuse me.

03:27.512 --> 03:28.545
Dr. Douglas Filmore.

03:28.630 --> 03:30.714
I'm here to examine the feet.

03:30.798 --> 03:31.932
I know him, Booth.

03:31.999 --> 03:33.150
Who?
Him.

03:33.217 --> 03:34.217
Dr. Filmore.

03:36.137 --> 03:37.688
How are you?

03:37.772 --> 03:39.389
Oh.

03:39.474 --> 03:41.975
Dr. Brennan,
it's, uh, been quite a while.

03:42.026 --> 03:43.143
Yes.

03:43.194 --> 03:44.361
Uh, excuse the left hand.

03:44.445 --> 03:47.180
I'm having some issues
with my right arm.

03:48.733 --> 03:52.035
So, you're here to examine
the remains as well, eh?

03:52.120 --> 03:53.036
Yes.

03:53.121 --> 03:54.237
Yes.

03:54.322 --> 03:56.373
Um, this is Special Agent
Seeley Booth, FBI.

03:56.457 --> 03:58.024
We're partners.
Nice to meet you.

03:58.076 --> 03:59.326
Pleasure.
So what happened

03:59.377 --> 04:01.244
to your arm?
It was Thursday, May 9.

04:01.329 --> 04:02.963
I was in my office
doing some reading,

04:03.030 --> 04:04.831
and my right arm
just ceased to function.

04:04.882 --> 04:06.717
The physicians
can't seem to find the cause.

04:06.784 --> 04:08.051
Very tough.
I'm sorry to hear that.

04:08.136 --> 04:10.837
Coincidentally,
I had just finished reading

04:10.888 --> 04:13.039
Dr. Brennan's
incredibly thorough

04:13.091 --> 04:15.892
repudiation of my attempts
to get my field of study

04:15.977 --> 04:17.894
recognized by the Board
of Forensic Scientists.

04:17.978 --> 04:18.928
Oh, boy. Oh...

04:19.012 --> 04:20.063
I-I work extremely hard

04:20.148 --> 04:21.180
on being thorough.

04:21.232 --> 04:23.216
It's gratifying
when someone notices.

04:23.267 --> 04:24.217
Thank you.

04:24.268 --> 04:25.902
You're welcome.

04:25.987 --> 04:28.438
So, w-what exactly
do you do again?

04:28.523 --> 04:30.857
Dr. Filmore calls himself a
forensic podiatrist even though

04:30.908 --> 04:33.777
that's not an officially
recognized discipline.

04:33.861 --> 04:36.830
Yes, I am merely
a board certified podiatrist

04:36.897 --> 04:38.582
who assists
law enforcement professionals

04:38.666 --> 04:40.033
by providing sound
podiatric analysis

04:40.084 --> 04:42.836
to forensic investigations.

04:42.903 --> 04:45.238
But I thank you
for correcting me, Dr. Brennan.

04:45.289 --> 04:47.374
You're very welcome.

04:47.425 --> 04:49.576
So, can you, uh, tell me

04:49.627 --> 04:51.077
how long these feet
have been in the river?

04:51.129 --> 04:52.078
No.
No.

04:52.130 --> 04:53.463
I need to take all of the feet

04:53.548 --> 04:55.382
back to the Jeffersonian
for further examination.

04:55.433 --> 04:57.934
Uh, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

04:58.019 --> 05:00.103
Excuse me. Would you be so good
as to point out for me

05:00.188 --> 05:02.556
the international boundary?

05:02.607 --> 05:06.059
Straight shot from that rock
over there to the border marker

05:06.110 --> 05:07.444
and right across the river.

05:07.528 --> 05:08.779
I see. So, I'm
sorry, I'm sorry.

05:08.863 --> 05:10.197
Okay, whoa, whoa, look.

05:10.264 --> 05:12.032
Pal, we're supposed to be
cooperating here, that's all.

05:12.099 --> 05:13.233
I'm sorry,
Dr. Brennan,

05:13.284 --> 05:15.101
but as far as we're
concerned, these are

05:15.153 --> 05:17.454
Canadian feet, and as such,
they will be examined

05:17.538 --> 05:21.575
by an ordinary,
garden-variety podiatrist.

05:21.626 --> 05:22.793
That's great.

05:22.877 --> 05:24.044
Now look what you've done.

05:24.111 --> 05:25.662
Thank you.

